{
  "stem": "833.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't think the accomplishments of the Jews would have been what they have been because what-- what-- if you look at the-- at the entire history of their accomplishments, of their contribution to the culture and to knowledge of the world-- when I went to--",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father used to say, you have to be twice as good as everybody else because you must never forget that you are Jewish.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jewish meant, of course, the tradition, the tradition of the Jewish society, which is of course age old.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They ask me, what is it?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What is it really?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, it's very difficult to put your finger on one thing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the outstanding of the Jewish tradition is the utter respect for knowledge, the utter respect for the written word, the respect for books, the respect for the accomplishment of the mind.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This is the guiding, and let's say, the innate thing of the Jewish tradition, regardless whether this has anything to do with religion or not.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In our case, it was not religion at all.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Religion was never-- never discussed at all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was allowed to stop religious lessons when I was 12.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that was actually the majority of the middle class in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The middle class in Vienna was agnostic.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, that was just about 50 years earlier.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My grandfather was a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My other grandfather was a cantor, my father's father, who he never knew, because he died when he was 60-- 60 years old.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I did never know him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My grandmother used to-- still keeps Jewish holidays in a certain way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I think she more or less declared what was really necessary to abide by the Jewish rules.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
